G. Flaminius inauspicato consul creatus : he was Tribune of the Plebs B.C. 232, and conqueror of the Insubres, a Gallie tribe in the north of Italy, B.C. 223. In the Insubrian VVar Flaminius received despatches from the Senate commanding him to return to Rome, as he had been elected consul without the proper religious ceremonies. Paying no attention to his orders, he engaged and defeated the enemy.

Fearing that a similar attempt might be made to oust him from the consulship, in B.C. 217 he left the city before the Ides of March, the customary day for entering upon office. No objection, however, was raised, and he proceeded to his post, this time with a different result.
